race.comment: Is today the day for PELEVECCHIO (3)? After a brilliant 3YO season, in which she finished sixth in the G1 Australasian Oaks, she hasn't really gone on with it this campaign. She's seemingly had her chance in recent runs but this is the best suited she's been all spring. Up to 1800m looks in her favour, as does the drop back to BM56 grade. Surely? GREATESTOFEASE (8) is chasing three wins on end and is an obvious danger. The 3kg claim helps her cause but she will need a good ride from the wide barrier. FANTASTIC HOST (11) mixes his form but his best is good enough to finish in the money. Others that appeal on an each-way basis include HARLEY'N'ROSE (5), who races well at this track, and CARING LASS (7), who is a last-start winner.
